explanation: Include each symbol because the target function itself does not call any string.h routines, so any potential violations must come from its callees or from how data/ids/tokens are passed to them. • OS_ObjectIdGetById — direct callee; its implementation may call string functions or write into the token pointer passed by address. • OS_BinSemTimedWait_Impl — direct callee; may call string functions further down. • OS_ObjectIdTransactionInit, OS_ObjectIdToArrayIndex, OS_ObjectIdConvertToken, OS_ObjectIdTransactionCancel — transitive callees of OS_ObjectIdGetById; their implementations may use string.h APIs or manipulate buffers derived from the token/id. • OS_Posix_CompAbsDelayTime, OS_GenericBinSemTake_Impl — transitive callees of OS_BinSemTimedWait_Impl; need to inspect them for string API usage. • OS_object_token_t — the token object is passed by pointer to callees; its definition/layout/size is required to determine whether any string operations on it could access out of bounds. • osal_id_t — the id parameter type may influence conversions or buffer indexing in callees. • uint32, int32 — parameter/return types used by the function; included for completeness when inspecting argument/return use in callees. • OS_LOCK_MODE_NONE, LOCAL_OBJID_TYPE — constants passed to OS_ObjectIdGetById that may alter internal code paths (and thus whether string functions are called). • OS_SUCCESS — used to test the return of OS_ObjectIdGetById; required to determine control flow to callees that might use string APIs.
